{"sections":[],"abstract":[{"text":"Frequently asked questions about FlyHUD.","type":"text"}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/flyhud\/faq"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/flyhud.FlyHUD\/documentation\/FlyHUD"]]},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/flyhud.FlyHUD\/documentation\/FlyHUD\/faq","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"seeAlsoSections":[{"anchor":"Reference","title":"Reference","identifiers":["doc:\/\/flyhud.FlyHUD\/documentation\/FlyHUD\/privacy","doc:\/\/flyhud.FlyHUD\/documentation\/FlyHUD\/benchmark","doc:\/\/flyhud.FlyHUD\/documentation\/FlyHUD\/release-notes","doc:\/\/flyhud.FlyHUD\/documentation\/FlyHUD\/CHANGELOG"],"generated":true}],"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"General","anchor":"General"},{"type":"heading","level":3,"text":"What is the difference between FlyHUD, FlyIndicatorHUD, and FlyProgressHUD?","anchor":"What-is-the-difference-between-FlyHUD-FlyIndicatorHUD-and-FlyProgressHUD"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"FlyHUD"}]},{"text":" — The core module containing the ","type":"text"},{"code":"HUD","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" class, layout system, animations,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"and background views. This is all you need for system indicators and custom views.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"FlyIndicatorHUD"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" — Provides custom activity indicator styles (ring clip, ball spin,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"circle stroke, arc dot). Depends on FlyHUD.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"FlyProgressHUD","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":" — Provides custom progress view styles (bar, round, annular, pie)."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Depends on FlyHUD."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can import only what you need. All three are independent of each other."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"heading","text":"Why was it renamed from LPHUD to FlyHUD?","anchor":"Why-was-it-renamed-from-LPHUD-to-FlyHUD","level":3},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The library was renamed in version 1.5.6 to better reflect its nature: “Fly” implies","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"fast, efficient, and flexible — consistent with the real-time nature of a HUD.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"heading","text":"Does FlyHUD support SwiftUI?","anchor":"Does-FlyHUD-support-SwiftUI","level":3},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Yes! The ","type":"text"},{"code":"FlyHUDSwiftUI","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" module provides native SwiftUI support with declarative modifiers:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","code":["import FlyHUDSwiftUI","","MyView()","    .hudLoading(isPresented: $isLoading, label: \"Loading...\")"],"syntax":"swift"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"See "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/flyhud.FlyHUD\/documentation\/FlyHUD\/swiftui-integration"},{"type":"text","text":" for complete documentation covering all API layers."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"heading","text":"Installation","anchor":"Installation","level":2},{"type":"heading","text":"Which module should I import?","anchor":"Which-module-should-I-import","level":3},{"type":"table","header":"row","rows":[[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Need"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Import","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"System spinner + custom views only"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"FlyHUD"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"SwiftUI declarative modifiers","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"FlyHUDSwiftUI","type":"codeVoice"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Custom indicator animations","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"FlyHUD","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" + ","type":"text"},{"code":"FlyIndicatorHUD","type":"codeVoice"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Custom progress styles"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"FlyHUD"},{"type":"text","text":" + "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"FlyProgressHUD"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"All features"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"All three"}]}]]]},{"anchor":"Can-I-use-only-CocoaPods-subspecs","level":3,"type":"heading","text":"Can I use only CocoaPods subspecs?"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Yes. Use subspecs to minimize dependencies:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["pod 'FlyHUD', :subspecs => ['FlyHUD']           # Core only","pod 'FlyHUD', :subspecs => ['FlyIndicatorHUD']  # Core + indicators","pod 'FlyHUD', :subspecs => ['FlyProgressHUD']   # Core + progress"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"ruby"},{"anchor":"Why-do-I-get-No-such-module-FlyHUD-in-my-Xcode-project","level":3,"type":"heading","text":"Why do I get “No such module ‘FlyHUD’” in my Xcode project?"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Ensure you have:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"orderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Added the SPM package dependency correctly","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Added the library product to your target’s “Frameworks, Libraries, and Embedded Content”"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Cleaned build folder (Shift+Cmd+K) and rebuilt"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"anchor":"Usage","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Usage"},{"anchor":"Why-does-my-HUD-stay-on-screen-forever","type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Why does my HUD stay on screen forever?"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Every ","type":"text"},{"code":"show()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" must be paired with a ","type":"text"},{"code":"hide()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". Common causes:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Forgetting to call "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"hide()"},{"type":"text","text":" on error paths"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Calling "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"hide()"},{"type":"text","text":" on a different HUD instance"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Using ","type":"text"},{"code":"isCountEnabled = true","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" without matching show\/hide pairs","type":"text"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"anchor":"Why-does-my-HUD-appear-behind-other-views","type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Why does my HUD appear behind other views?"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"HUD is added as a subview of the view you specify. Ensure no other views are added","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"after the HUD, or call ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"view.bringSubviewToFront(hud)"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Why-doesnt-the-keyboard-guide-work","type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Why doesn’t the keyboard guide work?"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Keyboard guide is iOS-only (not available on tvOS or visionOS)"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Ensure "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"HUD.keyboardGuide"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"hud.keyboardGuide"},{"type":"text","text":" is set to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".center()"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".bottom()"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The keyboard must actually appear (test with a focused text field)"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"text":"How do I show HUD on the full screen (over navigation bar)?","type":"heading","anchor":"How-do-I-show-HUD-on-the-full-screen-over-navigation-bar","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Add the HUD to the window instead of the view controller’s view:"}]},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["if let window = view.window {","    HUD.show(to: window)","}"]},{"text":"Can I show multiple HUDs simultaneously?","type":"heading","anchor":"Can-I-show-multiple-HUDs-simultaneously","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Yes. Each "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"HUD.show(to:)"},{"type":"text","text":" call creates a new HUD instance:"}]},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["let hud1 = HUD.show(to: view, label: \"Step 1\")","let hud2 = HUD.show(to: view, label: \"Step 2\")"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"code":"HUD.hideAll(for:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" to dismiss all at once."}]},{"text":"How do I update HUD content after showing?","type":"heading","anchor":"How-do-I-update-HUD-content-after-showing","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Access the HUD’s ","type":"text"},{"code":"contentView","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" to update labels, mode, or progress:","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["let hud = HUD.show(to: view)","\/\/ Later...","hud.contentView.label.text = \"Almost done...\"","hud.contentView.mode = .custom(checkmarkView)"]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Appearance","text":"Appearance"},{"type":"heading","level":3,"anchor":"How-do-I-change-the-HUDs-background-transparency","text":"How do I change the HUD’s background transparency?"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["\/\/ Content card background","hud.contentView.color = UIColor.black.withAlphaComponent(0.7)","","\/\/ Full-screen overlay","hud.backgroundView.color = UIColor.black.withAlphaComponent(0.3)","hud.backgroundView.style = .solidColor"]},{"type":"heading","level":3,"anchor":"How-do-I-make-the-HUD-largersmaller","text":"How do I make the HUD larger\/smaller?"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["\/\/ Set minimum size","hud.contentView.layout.minSize = CGSize(width: 150, height: 150)","","\/\/ Or adjust margins","hud.contentView.layout.hMargin = 30","hud.contentView.layout.vMargin = 30"]},{"type":"heading","level":3,"anchor":"Can-I-use-SF-Symbols-as-custom-views","text":"Can I use SF Symbols as custom views?"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Yes:"}]},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["let config = UIImage.SymbolConfiguration(pointSize: 30, weight: .medium)","let image = UIImage(systemName: \"wifi.exclamationmark\", withConfiguration: config)","let imageView = UIImageView(image: image)","HUD.showStatus(to: view, mode: .custom(imageView), label: \"No Connection\")"]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Threading","text":"Threading"},{"type":"heading","level":3,"anchor":"Is-FlyHUD-thread-safe","text":"Is FlyHUD thread-safe?"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"All HUD APIs must be called on the main thread. The library uses "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@MainActor"},{"type":"text","text":" isolation"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and debug assertions to enforce this. Background work should dispatch to main before"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"interacting with HUD:"}]},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["DispatchQueue.global().async {","    let result = heavyComputation()","    DispatchQueue.main.async {","        hud.contentView.label.text = result","        hud.hide()","    }","}"]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Migration","tex